  <glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>enabling factors</term><meaning>internal and external conditions directly related to the issue that help individuals or populations adopt and maintain healthy or unhealthy behaviors or lifestyle, or embrace or reject particular environmental conditions</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00002"><term>health promotion setting</term><meaning>the place or social context in which people engage in daily activities, in which environmental, organizational, and persona factors interact to affect health and well-being</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00003"><term>infodemic</term><meaning>an overabundance of information, including misinformation, that surges during a health emergency</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00004"><term>social listening</term><meaning>the process of gathering information about people’s questions and concerns and circulating narratives and misinformation about health from online and offline data sources</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
